postcontent:
If you haven't taken the time to contact your elected officials regarding your 2nd Amendment Rights please do so today. It is actually quite easy and shouldn't take more than a few minutes of your time.

First copy the text below and change it to reflect your own views OR write your own letter.

Next go to this address and complete the online forms 
http://www.nraila.org/get-involved-locally/grassroots/write-your-reps.aspx

Sample Letter-

I'm very concerned with the actions that many of your colleagues are taking in regard to the Rights of Law Abiding Citizens to buy, own or possess firearms. I understand your job as my elected official is to defend the Constitution and our 2nd Amendment Rights. To that end I am requesting you take a stand against any further actions of this nature. In the interest of brevity I will outline my position below.

1) I DO NOT support any type of weapons ban based on cosmetic features.

2) I DO NOT support any type of ban or limit on the capacity of magazines (clips).

3) I DO NOT support a national firearm registration of any kind.

4) I  DO believe that Pennsylvanians have nothing to fear from Law Abiding Gun Owners.

5) I Do believe that any actions taken to ban or limit firearms in the hands of good Pennsylvanians to be an unjust punishment for crimes we have not committed.

*I WILL NOT vote for or support any politician that will not stand for ALL of my 2nd Amendment Rights.

Thank you for your time,

title: For Sale:  Bravo Company (BCM) AR15 upper receiver  - NEW IN BOX!
postcontent:
One of the best uppers on the planet today. Very High quality, low production. Very hard to find... even on Gunbroker. The BCM barrels have been known to last 40,000+ rounds and many special forces military get these uppers from BCM. Over half of BCM sales is to the military and law enforcement. Google the reviews of these weapons and see for yourself. No trades. Cash only.


M4 Feed Ramp Barrel Extension

•
 M4 Feed Ramp Flat Top Receiver 

•
 T-Marked Upper Receivers 

•
 USGI 1/7 Twist Rates 

•
 USGI 5.56 NATO Chambers 

•
 Mil-Spec 11595E - Certified Barrel Steel (CMV) 

•
 Chrome Lined Bore and Chamber 

•
 Manganese Phosphate Barrel Finish 

•
 Mil-Spec F-Marked Forged Front Sights 

•
 USGI Government Profile Barrels 

•
 HPT (High Pressure Test) Barrels 

•
 MPI (Magnetic Particle Inspected) Barrels
 Made by Bravo Company MFG, Inc. (BCM) These Barreled Upper Receiver Groups are designed for shooting professionals with the Mil-Spec features for the demands of their duty. They are fully assembled, headspaced, and test fired. These do not include bolt carrier groups or charging handles.

  As a note: BCM barrel components are parkerized separately before assembly. Prior to shipping, all BCM upper receiver groups are test fired for function, laser bore sighted with a Milspec carry handle for sight alignment within Mil-Specs, and then batch samples are test fired for accuracy. As such, the upper receiver group will show handling marks consistant with these quality control procedures.


 M4 Feed Ramp Barrel Extension (USGI) M4 Feed Ramp Flat Top Receiver

 In developing the USGI M4 carbine as one of the primary weapons for today’s infantry, some modifications were performed to the original M16 platform to enhance the reliability of the shorter barreled carbines. With the shorter carbine gas system and the increased gas port pressure, the carbine cycled faster, and at times the cycle rate could be faster than the magazine would feed ammunition. One of the modifications done to increase reliable feeding included enhancing the angle and the length of the feed ramps. This USGI modification was done to both the barrel extension and the upper receiver, creating a longer and steeper feed ramp. These Mil-Spec M4 feed ramps are part of the original CNC manufacturing process. As a result, the factory machined M4 feed ramps on the receiver are hard coat anodized which adds significant strength to the aluminum. This feature is offered on all BCM uppers and all BCM barrels. 

T-Marked Upper Receiver 

The contemporary M16/M4 rifle is built around the concept of modularity. All of the BCM flat top uppers feature a USGI type laser etched T-marks to provide addressing for the remounting of tactical accessories such as optics, laser sights, etc. This enables the weapon platform to be easily configured and then accurately reconfigured for each specific mission. 

USGI 1/7 Twist Rate 

The USGI 1/7 twist rate of all of the BCM barrels is the preferred twist rate by most professional infantryman. This twist rate has proven very versatile and can effectively run the new heavier 5.56 ammo that is hugely popular with military and private security personal for its’ superior ballistics. 

Mil-Spec 11595E - Barrel Steel 

BCM barrel steel is Mil-Spec per MIL-B-11595E. This grade (CMV) of steel is a Mil-Spec steel used in the USGI M16 family of rifles; it is stronger and will last longer than the typical barrels offered in the commercial market. The Mil-Spec grade steel gets its’ additional strength and rigidity from an increase in carbon and/or vanadium in the alloy. This will offer increased barrel life and performance through use in all types of extreme environments and temperatures.


Chrome Bore and Chamber 

One of the first modifications that were made to the original M16 in the mid 1960’s was the addition of the chrome lined bore and chamber. It is now a world wide standard in the industry for a battle rifle. The chrome bore and chamber is harder than the barrel steel and on the USGI M16/M4 rifles will aid in chambering, extraction, and reliability. It increases velocity, and also resist against fouling and corrosion from extended use in the field. This gives the end user a longer barrel life with less required time in maintenance and cleaning. 

Manganese Phosphate Barrel Finish 

Barrels are parkerized with the manganese phosphate finish (Mil-Spec A-A-59267). Military specifications also state that the entire barrel surface is phosphate finished to create a porous surface to absorb oil as to resist against corrosion from the elements. BCM barrels are phosphated before installation of front sights. This is a much more extensive assembly operation, but insures that the entire barrel is finished and protected . . .even under the front sight base. 

5.56 NATO Chambers 

The USGI 5.56 NATO chamber is the best choice for effective deployment, reliability, and compatibility, of higher chamber pressures of military ammo. 

Mil-Spec F-Marked Forged Front Sight Bases 

Mil-Spec for rifles issued to the troops require taller front sight bases on all flat top AR rifles. Many commercial offerings use M16A2 height front sight bases on all of their barrels regardless of what type of upper it is installed on. As a result, owners of rifles and carbines with the flat top receiver configuration can have problems getting a proper 'zero' for elevation with Mil-Spec back up iron sights. As all of the BCM uppers are built for flat top uppers, all have the proper Mil-Spec F marked front sight base to insure the correct height for iron sight zeroing when using military iron sights. Mil-Spec taper pins secure the forged front sight base with the sling swivel secured by tubular rivets. 

Government Barrel Profiles 

Duty rifles are built to be carried - day in and day out. The USGI barrel profiles (often referred to as the Government Profile) enable the operator to carry their weapon for longer periods of time and deploy them faster than the heavier commercial H-Barrel counterparts. The government profile barrel is also compatible with the current M203 mounting systems. 

HPT / MP Inspected Barrels 

Military specifications require that barrels undergo a HPT (High-Pressure Test) load as a part of quality assurance procedures. Commonly referred to as a proof load, the M197 HPT is rated for 70,000 psi. BCM barrels are proof loaded and then MPI (Magnetic Particle Inspected) to detect any possible flaws in the barrels surface. The barrels are MP inspected with both circular and longitudinal magnetic fields per ASTME1444-01 (current Mil-Spec) to assure a high quality finished product. All BCM barrels are marked HP MP as our proof load marking.

title: For Sale:  Browning 1919 belt-fed, semi-auto, in 7.62 NATO, w/ Crankfire !!!
postcontent:
Allied Armament made this from a real US Browning machinegun that was sold to the Israelis, who converted it from .30 US (.30-06) to 7.62 NATO. The gun was imported back to the US without the right sideplate, which is legally the “frame” on this gun. AA made a new sideplate and replaced a few parts in the trigger linkage so that it is semi-auto only so, if you can own a rifle, you can own this. 

A really nice feature about Allied Armament is that they received permission to mark their name on the inside of the gun and reproduced the original General Motors, Saginaw Gear Division markings on the outside. So, other than the few Israeli marks designating the new caliber, this looks like a brand new 1940’s military machinegun. 

The gun comes mounted on a new M2 medium tripod and a really cool reproduction bronze pintle mount and T&E mechanism, giving it a cool pre-war look. 

Here’s where it’s gets really cool. Included in this package is a brand new Emory Jones Crankfire adapter, which is also no longer in production. This allows you to shoot either single fire with a thumb trigger or use the crank to spit out 7.62 at 470 rounds per minute!!! (keep in mind that the 1919 doesn’t have a quick change barrel so the sustained rate of fire is 75rpm). “Gatling type mechanisms do not fall under NFA so this completely legal to own, if you can own a single shot .22 rifle.  

If you don’t want to lug this beast around old school (a good way to have even more respect for those from the Old Corps), This will come in a used but, very good condition Hardigg Storm Case iM3300; that comes with a new foam insert set you can custom cut to fit your new gun & accessories perfectly. Best of all this is the wheeled model : ) 

If you order now, I’ll include a WWII, US, M1 ammo box, which could use refurbishing but overall very good condition. It will have about 300 reusable links and 100 rounds to get you started.  Other than the case & ammo can, everything is brand new and only used for indoor display

Compared to the $20,000 price tag for a full auto 1919 with the bonus joy of having the BATF become your best buddy, this is a deal at $4,995. 
Willing to travel a bit, ship (realize this will be costly), & I’d consider partial trades too (not limited to: 20 or 28 o/u, .308 carbines, SAA 2nd & 3rd gen .38/.357 4¾“, Python, Manurhin, Sig 556 or P-210, S&W .22.32.38/357 revolvers, Stinger 22, SVD, Whitney Wolverine, or anything cool…), I'm a C&R and could receive appropriate guns however, this is not C&R eligible & if going out of state would need to transfer through an FFL.

title: For Sale:  Musgrave 98 Mauser 7x57
postcontent: Musgrave, 98 Mauser, 7x57 mauser, LOP 14 1/8", built on 1908 German Mauser action by Musgrave, a South African company, in their custom shop for Dr. Lucas Potgieter.  At the time this rifle was made Musgrave was contracted to build rifles for Rigby of London.  Dr. Potgieter owned the Powder Keg (Kruitvat) gun shop in Johannesburg, South Afric. He wrote several books on African hunting and hunting cartridges.  I have owned this gun since 1990.  It has some features of Rigby.   Lucas P. is written on the side of the barrel.  I hunted in Zimbabwe with this gun taking impala, warthog, kudu and sable as well as American whitetail and Canadian black bear.  It has a hinged floorplate, reverse claw mounts, quarter rib with one standing rear sight and 3 folding, rubber pad marked Musgrave.  It is stocked with english walnut, has a checkered pistol grip and fore end and ebony grip cap, ramped front sight with removable front blade, Swarovski 6x42 1" tube.  Light handling marks on wood, oil finish, no rust or pitting. Classic plainsgame rifle handles heavy bullets very well. Very good condition.
